1
00:00:21,670 --> 00:00:22,650
Because I

2
00:00:23,510 --> 00:00:24,850
watched it happen—

3
00:00:25,550 --> 00:00:26,900
those dozen miners

4
00:00:28,350 --> 00:00:29,420
went down the shaft...

5
00:00:37,240 --> 00:00:39,370
I don't know how far

6
00:00:39,390 --> 00:00:41,820
that lift fell.

7
00:00:42,030 --> 00:00:42,940
Dad!

8
00:00:43,350 --> 00:00:43,900
Dad!

9
00:00:44,430 --> 00:00:44,940
Dad!

10
00:00:45,390 --> 00:00:45,900
Dad!

11
00:00:49,960 --> 00:00:52,010
You know how deep that mine is?

12
00:00:53,430 --> 00:00:54,690
How bad was this accident?

13
00:00:55,880 --> 00:00:57,650
How many people
won't make it out this time?

14
00:02:26,880 --> 00:02:31,080
[In the Name of Justice]

15
00:02:31,080 --> 00:02:34,080
[Episode 23]

16
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:41,540
We're working to confirm
the exact number of casualties.

17
00:02:42,750 --> 00:02:43,730
Right after the accident,

18
00:02:43,960 --> 00:02:46,610
emergency crews, police, EMTs,

19
00:02:46,630 --> 00:02:49,340
and firefighters were on the scene.

20
00:02:49,710 --> 00:02:51,940
Rescue efforts are ongoing.

21
00:02:52,910 --> 00:02:54,340
As you can see in this footage...

22
00:02:54,360 --> 00:02:54,690
Hello?

23
00:02:55,150 --> 00:02:55,500
Mr. Chen?

24
00:02:56,080 --> 00:02:56,980
There was an accident at the mine.

25
00:02:57,590 --> 00:02:58,340
Did you know?

26
00:02:59,190 --> 00:03:00,260
What's it got to do with you?

27
00:03:00,960 --> 00:03:01,820
Mind your own business.

28
00:03:02,150 --> 00:03:02,980
The mine was

29
00:03:03,080 --> 00:03:05,100
supposed to be shut down,

30
00:03:05,560 --> 00:03:06,980
but management ignored the order

31
00:03:07,150 --> 00:03:08,540
and forced everyone to keep working.

32
00:03:09,310 --> 00:03:11,290
The cause is still under investigation.

33
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:12,570
Sheng,

34
00:03:13,190 --> 00:03:14,060
is there

35
00:03:16,430 --> 00:03:17,380
any way

36
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:21,100
I can distance myself from Mr. Chen?

37
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:22,730
Mr. Chen...

38
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:26,730
Seriously,

39
00:03:27,710 --> 00:03:28,130
man,

40
00:03:29,310 --> 00:03:30,410
is there any way

41
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,500
I can distance myself from you?

42
00:03:37,430 --> 00:03:38,130
Is it him or not?

43
00:03:39,190 --> 00:03:40,260
Just tell me, is it him?

44
00:03:41,280 --> 00:03:42,500
Can you honestly say it's not?

45
00:03:42,800 --> 00:03:43,940
Has he gone insane?

46
00:03:44,520 --> 00:03:45,570
That's murder!

47
00:03:45,680 --> 00:03:46,540
Major crime!

48
00:03:47,150 --> 00:03:48,570
Sooner or later, we'll be implicated!

49
00:03:50,800 --> 00:03:51,220
Yu,

50
00:03:51,840 --> 00:03:52,500
I'm telling you,

51
00:03:53,120 --> 00:03:54,170
starting now,

52
00:03:54,360 --> 00:03:56,060
he can't be part
of anything we're doing!

53
00:03:56,400 --> 00:03:57,980
We're running things from now on.

54
00:04:02,190 --> 00:04:03,220
Say something!

55
00:04:05,030 --> 00:04:06,730
Can you keep him in check or not?!

56
00:04:07,710 --> 00:04:08,010
You...

57
00:05:02,720 --> 00:05:03,170
Hello, sir.

58
00:05:03,600 --> 00:05:04,850
License and registration, please.

59
00:05:12,630 --> 00:05:13,850
Stop the car!

60
00:05:14,430 --> 00:05:14,850
Pull over!

61
00:05:15,920 --> 00:05:16,340
Stop looking.

62
00:05:38,070 --> 00:05:40,410
I went to their winch workshop.

63
00:05:41,630 --> 00:05:43,340
The winch hooks right up to the lift.

64
00:05:44,600 --> 00:05:45,220
So,

65
00:05:46,160 --> 00:05:46,900
after I loosened

66
00:05:46,920 --> 00:05:49,490
the bolts on the brake pads,

67
00:05:51,160 --> 00:05:53,540
the fluid started spraying everywhere—

68
00:05:54,070 --> 00:05:54,900
soaked me head to toe.

69
00:05:55,800 --> 00:05:56,780
And it wouldn't stop.

70
00:05:57,310 --> 00:05:57,980
It just kept coming.

71
00:05:59,240 --> 00:06:00,050
I didn't dare stick around.

72
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:02,100
I got out of there as fast as I could.

73
00:06:03,830 --> 00:06:04,780
I knew as soon

74
00:06:05,750 --> 00:06:08,780
as that brake fluid was gone,

75
00:06:09,560 --> 00:06:12,490
the lift would break loose!

76
00:06:13,920 --> 00:06:15,810
Straight freefall.
The whole thing would crash.

77
00:07:03,270 --> 00:07:04,730
Right now,

78
00:07:04,750 --> 00:07:06,810
I don't know how far

79
00:07:06,830 --> 00:07:09,340
that lift fell.

80
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:10,980
Long,

81
00:07:12,240 --> 00:07:14,290
You know how deep that mine is?

82
00:07:15,680 --> 00:07:16,930
How bad was this accident?

83
00:07:18,070 --> 00:07:19,170
How many people
won't make it out this time?

84
00:07:20,190 --> 00:07:21,580
I'm asking you!

85
00:07:22,750 --> 00:07:24,460
How many people will die?

86
00:07:25,800 --> 00:07:26,200
Here.

87
00:07:27,510 --> 00:07:27,980
Take a sip.

88
00:07:36,560 --> 00:07:36,930
Listen,

89
00:07:39,750 --> 00:07:40,780
everyone's got their own fate.

90
00:07:42,800 --> 00:07:43,850
Don't let this eat you up.

91
00:07:46,000 --> 00:07:47,290
I told you before,

92
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:49,020
don't go about things

93
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:50,370
like this!

94
00:07:50,390 --> 00:07:51,340
But you had to push it!

95
00:07:52,190 --> 00:07:53,580
Now there's no turning back!

96
00:07:53,800 --> 00:07:54,370
Back to where?

97
00:07:55,950 --> 00:07:57,050
To Mr. Yu!

98
00:08:00,270 --> 00:08:00,700
Well,

99
00:08:02,800 --> 00:08:04,290
I never intended to go back anyway.

100
00:08:05,870 --> 00:08:07,370
That's why I did what I did.

101
00:08:09,040 --> 00:08:09,610
Think about it,

102
00:08:10,630 --> 00:08:11,610
they've halted the auction.

103
00:08:12,720 --> 00:08:14,290
Jiang Yuan can't get the mine,

104
00:08:15,630 --> 00:08:16,930
so it's ours.

105
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,290
Mr. Yu

106
00:08:20,190 --> 00:08:22,540
must know we're behind this.

107
00:08:24,240 --> 00:08:26,250
So what do we say if he asks?

108
00:08:26,510 --> 00:08:27,250
Why bother?

109
00:08:29,750 --> 00:08:30,930
He already knows.

110
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:34,300
Let's just come clean,

111
00:08:36,550 --> 00:08:38,460
see if he still backs Jiang Yuan now.

112
00:08:44,750 --> 00:08:46,420
Dad!

113
00:08:47,390 --> 00:08:48,820
Dad!

114
00:08:50,390 --> 00:08:51,420
Dad!

115
00:08:53,630 --> 00:08:55,100
Dad!

116
00:09:20,150 --> 00:09:20,580
Sir.

117
00:09:21,320 --> 00:09:21,650
Come in.

118
00:09:27,270 --> 00:09:27,890
Hello, sir.

119
00:09:28,790 --> 00:09:29,100
Take a seat.

120
00:09:30,480 --> 00:09:31,850
I'd rather not, thanks.

121
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:33,460
Your blood pressure's already high,

122
00:09:33,790 --> 00:09:34,460
don't get so worked up.

123
00:09:35,360 --> 00:09:36,300
It doesn't help, does it?

124
00:09:37,440 --> 00:09:38,180
It's not like I want to,

125
00:09:38,510 --> 00:09:39,650
problems just keep piling up.

126
00:09:41,960 --> 00:09:43,370
I've made some calls.

127
00:09:44,750 --> 00:09:45,300
Don't worry,

128
00:09:46,150 --> 00:09:48,250
the government's already
launching an investigation.

129
00:09:48,550 --> 00:09:50,370
Can I just ask one thing?

130
00:09:51,200 --> 00:09:51,940
Given everything that's happened,

131
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:53,420
what kind of legal trouble

132
00:09:54,750 --> 00:09:56,130
is my son facing?

133
00:09:56,600 --> 00:09:57,300
Too early to say.

134
00:09:57,910 --> 00:09:58,700
The police are still looking into it.

135
00:10:01,750 --> 00:10:02,220
Wan Hai,

136
00:10:03,150 --> 00:10:04,180
let's just chat.

137
00:10:06,200 --> 00:10:08,460
How long have you owned that mine?

138
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,010
Why do you ask?

139
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:15,250
Just curious.

140
00:10:17,790 --> 00:10:20,130
Maybe 20 years or so.

141
00:10:22,150 --> 00:10:23,420
That mine's always been busy, huh?

142
00:10:24,720 --> 00:10:27,060
There was a shooting there
over a decade ago.

143
00:10:27,720 --> 00:10:28,530
Two people died.

144
00:10:30,030 --> 00:10:30,980
I'm sure you haven't forgotten.

145
00:10:34,000 --> 00:10:35,890
Turns out, that case was mishandled.

146
00:10:39,870 --> 00:10:41,100
The shooter back then

147
00:10:41,790 --> 00:10:43,340
wasn't Sun Yihu, was it?

148
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,250
I couldn't say.

149
00:10:45,790 --> 00:10:46,610
But I do know

150
00:10:47,600 --> 00:10:48,370
there were two guys involved.

151
00:10:48,750 --> 00:10:50,370
One got convicted, named Dahu.

152
00:10:50,840 --> 00:10:53,060
Jiang Hongjun was the one in charge.

153
00:10:53,080 --> 00:10:54,490
If you want answers, ask him.

154
00:11:00,750 --> 00:11:01,940
Did you know Qiao's dead?

155
00:11:04,150 --> 00:11:06,010
Why bring this up?

156
00:11:06,390 --> 00:11:07,530
What are you getting at?

157
00:11:08,390 --> 00:11:09,850
Before Qiao died,

158
00:11:10,270 --> 00:11:12,100
he was digging into
the Wanchuan Mining Shooting.

159
00:11:22,360 --> 00:11:22,880
[Thirteen Years Ago]

160
00:11:22,880 --> 00:11:23,340
Hey,

161
00:11:23,870 --> 00:11:24,610
I'm right next door.

162
00:11:24,790 --> 00:11:25,420
Let me know

163
00:11:26,390 --> 00:11:26,940
if you need anything.

164
00:11:27,550 --> 00:11:27,980
Alright.

165
00:11:28,550 --> 00:11:29,700
Okay, I'll let you guys work.

166
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:34,650
What are you up to?

167
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,370
Get them some water.

168
00:11:43,960 --> 00:11:44,340
Yang,

169
00:11:44,840 --> 00:11:45,650
since I'm already here,

170
00:11:46,030 --> 00:11:47,300
can I get paid now?

171
00:11:48,270 --> 00:11:48,820
No problem.

172
00:11:50,510 --> 00:11:51,250
Pay him first.

173
00:11:59,960 --> 00:12:00,610
Wan Hai!

174
00:12:01,030 --> 00:12:01,820
What is it?

175
00:12:06,960 --> 00:12:08,340
What's with the firecrackers in here?

176
00:12:08,910 --> 00:12:10,460
Wan Hai's here!

177
00:12:14,160 --> 00:12:15,240
[Finance Office]

178
00:12:36,320 --> 00:12:37,420
Wan Hai!

179
00:12:41,080 --> 00:12:41,940
What else do you know

180
00:12:42,840 --> 00:12:43,650
about that shooting?

181
00:12:49,440 --> 00:12:51,010
Nothing, I swear.

182
00:12:52,120 --> 00:12:53,530
I'm feeling a bit dizzy...

183
00:13:18,910 --> 00:13:20,180
After they closed our mine,

184
00:13:21,200 --> 00:13:21,850
Chao

185
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:24,610
was desperate to reopen,

186
00:13:25,390 --> 00:13:26,180
but the Mining Bureau

187
00:13:26,600 --> 00:13:27,770
wouldn't even talk to us.

188
00:13:27,910 --> 00:13:29,100
Has

189
00:13:29,630 --> 00:13:30,370
that lift of yours

190
00:13:31,550 --> 00:13:32,980
ever had problems before?

191
00:13:33,200 --> 00:13:33,650
Never.

192
00:13:34,120 --> 00:13:35,890
It was always kept in perfect condition.

193
00:13:36,200 --> 00:13:36,650
You sure?

194
00:13:37,120 --> 00:13:37,580
Definitely.

195
00:13:39,000 --> 00:13:40,770
We do regular maintenance checks.

196
00:13:40,960 --> 00:13:42,100
Regular maintenance checks?

197
00:13:44,030 --> 00:13:44,890
When was the last one?

198
00:13:46,030 --> 00:13:46,820
What date,

199
00:13:47,200 --> 00:13:47,730
what time?

200
00:13:48,630 --> 00:13:49,650
What did you check?

201
00:13:49,960 --> 00:13:51,420
I know how things work over there.

202
00:13:52,360 --> 00:13:53,010
"Regular checks"? Yeah right!

203
00:13:56,910 --> 00:13:59,220
Have you seen Wan Chao
since the accident?

204
00:14:00,030 --> 00:14:00,420
No.

205
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,940
Honestly, I'm more worried than you are.

206
00:14:03,720 --> 00:14:04,980
Where could he be,

207
00:14:05,000 --> 00:14:05,820
with everything that's happened?

208
00:14:06,480 --> 00:14:07,340
It all happened so fast.

209
00:14:07,390 --> 00:14:09,420
When's the last time you saw him?

210
00:14:09,870 --> 00:14:10,300
Where were you?

211
00:14:11,240 --> 00:14:12,220
I guess...

212
00:14:13,510 --> 00:14:14,060
Yesterday.

213
00:14:15,240 --> 00:14:16,730
We spoke on the phone yesterday.

214
00:14:18,000 --> 00:14:20,180
It's my fault. We argued

215
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:21,850
a couple days back,

216
00:14:22,390 --> 00:14:23,770
tried to meet up but he wouldn't see me.

217
00:14:24,750 --> 00:14:26,010
Now this disaster hits,

218
00:14:26,630 --> 00:14:28,220
and I have no clue where he is.

219
00:14:28,240 --> 00:14:29,490
If anything's

220
00:14:30,080 --> 00:14:31,300
happened to him,

221
00:14:32,870 --> 00:14:33,770
how could I ever live with myself?

222
00:14:34,240 --> 00:14:35,700
Are you saying

223
00:14:36,480 --> 00:14:38,610
Wan Chao hasn't been at the mine lately?

224
00:14:40,150 --> 00:14:40,820
I don't know.

225
00:14:42,030 --> 00:14:42,530
I don't know

226
00:14:43,440 --> 00:14:44,300
anything for sure right now.

227
00:14:45,320 --> 00:14:46,420
I just hope

228
00:14:46,440 --> 00:14:47,730
no more people die at that mine.

229
00:14:48,550 --> 00:14:50,340
If they do, the Wan family

230
00:14:50,360 --> 00:14:51,010
is finished for good.

231
00:14:51,840 --> 00:14:53,730
You're not allowed
to leave Dongping while we investigate,

232
00:14:54,080 --> 00:14:54,610
understood?

233
00:14:55,320 --> 00:14:55,980
Sure,

234
00:14:56,630 --> 00:14:57,420
I'm not going anywhere.

235
00:14:57,600 --> 00:14:58,850
And if Wan Chao contacts you,

236
00:14:59,360 --> 00:15:00,250
you tell us immediately.

237
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:01,300
Sure,

238
00:15:01,720 --> 00:15:02,100
I will.

239
00:15:10,440 --> 00:15:12,060
Everyone, the municipal party committee

240
00:15:12,870 --> 00:15:14,530
held an emergency meeting
right after the accident.

241
00:15:16,120 --> 00:15:17,340
We've gathered you here

242
00:15:17,750 --> 00:15:18,580
to go over

243
00:15:19,270 --> 00:15:20,100
their decisions

244
00:15:21,270 --> 00:15:22,340
and outline

245
00:15:22,910 --> 00:15:23,580
our next steps.

246
00:15:24,390 --> 00:15:25,010
Liu Yun,

247
00:15:25,630 --> 00:15:26,490
can you give us

248
00:15:27,030 --> 00:15:28,060
an update on the casualties?

249
00:15:28,790 --> 00:15:29,980
Seven miners are injured,

250
00:15:30,790 --> 00:15:31,700
but out of danger.

251
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:33,180
Six are still in critical condition,

252
00:15:33,440 --> 00:15:34,130
fighting for their lives.

253
00:15:34,720 --> 00:15:36,300
Two were found with

254
00:15:37,030 --> 00:15:38,180
no signs of life when rescued.

255
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:40,180
For the time being,

256
00:15:41,720 --> 00:15:42,650
our top priority is helping the victims.

257
00:15:43,150 --> 00:15:44,610
Make sure they get urgent care.

258
00:15:44,630 --> 00:15:46,460
Liu Yun, I'm counting on you.

259
00:15:47,120 --> 00:15:47,490
Understood.

260
00:15:48,720 --> 00:15:49,300
Yanwu,

261
00:15:50,480 --> 00:15:51,490
any word on the cause?

262
00:15:53,000 --> 00:15:54,770
Preliminary investigation suggests

263
00:15:54,790 --> 00:15:56,650
the hoist system of the lifting cage

264
00:15:56,870 --> 00:15:58,340
was worn out,

265
00:15:58,790 --> 00:15:59,850
creating major safety risks.

266
00:16:00,440 --> 00:16:01,730
That's what caused the lift to fail

267
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:03,180
while it was in use.

268
00:16:26,870 --> 00:16:28,250
Duo's so little.

269
00:16:28,270 --> 00:16:30,700
Yeah, she's basically still a baby.

270
00:16:31,120 --> 00:16:31,820
Hello?

271
00:16:32,000 --> 00:16:32,820
Ms. Zhang Wenjing?

272
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,010
It's Wan Chao.

273
00:16:35,270 --> 00:16:36,220
I need your help.

274
00:16:37,440 --> 00:16:38,180
Chao?

275
00:16:38,480 --> 00:16:39,580
I saw the news.

276
00:16:39,790 --> 00:16:40,820
What happened this time?

277
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,370
Ms. Zhang,

278
00:16:43,320 --> 00:16:44,220
can you help me?

279
00:16:46,080 --> 00:16:47,250
How?

280
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:49,530
Go ask

281
00:16:50,030 --> 00:16:51,700
the local authorities.

282
00:16:53,510 --> 00:16:54,300
You know better than anyone

283
00:16:54,320 --> 00:16:56,180
my dad was framed by those people.

284
00:16:56,270 --> 00:16:58,530
Local cops now have me
on the wanted list!

285
00:16:58,550 --> 00:17:00,060
How am I supposed to trust them?

286
00:17:00,150 --> 00:17:01,370
I know you're a good lawyer.

287
00:17:01,750 --> 00:17:03,370
It wasn't easy getting through to you,

288
00:17:03,670 --> 00:17:04,050
you've got to...

289
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:36,900
Ma'am,

290
00:17:37,750 --> 00:17:38,530
can I ask you about someone?

291
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:40,220
Have you seen this guy?

292
00:17:40,350 --> 00:17:40,980
No.

293
00:18:03,880 --> 00:18:04,380
Pick up!

294
00:18:05,310 --> 00:18:05,860
Come on!

295
00:18:28,270 --> 00:18:29,940
- Wan Chao, there's nothing I can do.
- I have proof!

296
00:18:30,440 --> 00:18:31,140
I have proof!

297
00:18:31,960 --> 00:18:32,420
The mine accident

298
00:18:33,070 --> 00:18:34,460
was sabotage.

299
00:18:35,920 --> 00:18:36,660
There's a cop

300
00:18:37,960 --> 00:18:38,860
who tampered with the crime scene

301
00:18:39,270 --> 00:18:40,090
and covered things up.

302
00:18:40,310 --> 00:18:40,940
I have it on video.

303
00:18:41,160 --> 00:18:41,490
And

304
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:43,250
it's been three years now.

305
00:18:43,880 --> 00:18:44,460
Ms. Zhang,

306
00:18:45,750 --> 00:18:47,050
they set my dad up as a gangster

307
00:18:47,070 --> 00:18:49,010
just to take the mine from us.

308
00:18:49,640 --> 00:18:50,570
You tried to help him

309
00:18:51,030 --> 00:18:52,420
and they called you a gangster too.

310
00:18:52,440 --> 00:18:53,180
Now I try,

311
00:18:53,200 --> 00:18:54,940
